# Google Places API (New) — powers the live reviews on the Contact page.
# Without these, the reviews section falls back to a "Read our Google reviews"
# link-out band, so the page still works.
#
# Setup:
#   1. Google Cloud Console → create/select a project, enable BILLING.
#   2. APIs & Services → enable "Places API (New)".
#   3. Credentials → create an API key. Restrict it to "Places API (New)".
#      (For a server key, restrict by IP or leave app-restriction "None";
#       do NOT expose this key to the browser.)
#   4. Find the Place ID for The Chigwell Marquees:
#      https://developers.google.com/maps/documentation/places/web-service/place-id
#
# Add both to Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables (Production).
GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_PLACE_ID=

# Dev-only: preview the live review-card layout locally with sample data.
# .env.local only (gitignored) — never set this on Vercel.
# GOOGLE_REVIEWS_PREVIEW=1
